      About this item

      • [Voice Control and 0%-100% Dimming] Dimmable plug can be controlled by voice. New One smart dimmer plug is compatible with Alexa, Google Assistant and Smart Life. You can adjust the brightness of the light as you like. "Alexa, set the table lamp to 80%"
      • [Easy Setup] So easy to use. New One dimmable smart plug need to connect to Smart Life and matches with 2.4ghz wifi, the network transmission is stable without dropping
      • [Schedule and Timer] The custom time feature understands you better. Dimmable timer is able to control the on or off according to the schedule you set. In this way dimming plugs can help you save on unnecessary costs
      • [Compact Design] The compact design allows one standard socket to be equipped with two dimmable smart outlets at the same time. Convenient and compact, easy to store
      • [Remote Control] Smart dimmer plug can be controlled by APP anytime and anywhere. After the plug is connected to 2.4G WiFi, you can control appliances to turn on or off even when you are outdoors. Rated current 15A, voltage 125V
      • [ETL/FCC Certified] New One smart dimmer outlet is ETL and FCC certified, ensuring safety and quality. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us. We will do our best to solve the problem

          Compact Design

          The size of the smart dimmer plug is designed to limit space and you can use 2 dimmable smart plugs at the same time in a standard outlet

          Mini Size

          Length: 2.52 inches

          Width: 1.14 inches

          Height: 1.46 inches

          LED Color

          Blue: Match successful

          Purple: Distributing network

          Red: overheating protection

          FCC Certified

          The product has passed FCC certification to protect your smart furniture.

          • Will this work on a 5Ghz Wifi?

            No, it cannot be connected to a 5Ghz WiFI network, only can be connected to 2.4Ghz WiFi network.

          • How Connect to Alexa?

            1) Add the dimmable smart plug to Smart Life first.

            2) Go to the Alexa APP and then Add the smart dimmer plug to Alexa.

            3) Search Smart Life and then link account.

            4) When the linking completed, you could control the Wi-Fi plug with Alexa.

          • Is it possible to use several of these outlets inside the house and control each one individually?

            Yes. Each smart plug and each individual outlet can be controlled separately.

          • Which lights can be used this dimm plug?

            It is compatible with dimmable LED lamps, bulbs, CFLs, halogen, incandescent, string and fluorescent lamps, Its load power must be less than 300W.

          • Will it restart automatically after power outage?

            Yes, once the WIFI connection is re-established, it will remember the previous settings and start working.

          How customer reviews and ratings work

          Customer Reviews, including Product Star Ratings help customers to learn more about the product and decide whether it is the right product for them.

          To calculate the overall star rating and percentage breakdown by star, we dont use a simple average. Instead, our system considers things like how recent a review is and if the reviewer bought the item on Amazon. It also analyzed reviews to verify trustworthiness.

          Amazon Customer
          5 out of 5 stars
          A dimmable plug module with a solid build
          I had a houseful of Insteon controllers for 10 years until they went belly up and I switched to Kasa-TP Link after a lot of research. Now I have a houseful of Kasa switches, plugs & bulbs to control 30 devices. I have 4 can lights on a single switch and I wanted to switch them separately so I needed a dimming module that would fit inside the can light. Kasa does not sell a dimming plug so after tons of research I chose the "New One" product line. This was a good choice. It fits inside the can, literally dims from 0 to 100%, and seems to be very well made.For those that are wondering, I converted one of the cans to a spotlight using a can version kit and an LED spotlight to light up a piece of artwork. In order to dim it I screwed a "socket-to-plug adapter" FROM the fixture INTO the dimming module and a "plug-to-socket adapter" from the dimming module to the light. Kinda crazy but it's safe and it works.
